     Control Constructs  (statement prefixes)

1. for(initial; condition; update)
     statement

Example:
  int i;
  for(i=1; i<=10; i++)
     printf("%d\n", i);


2. while(condition)
     statement
  int i = 1;                   int i = 1;
  while (i<=10) {              while (i<=10)
    printf("%d\n", i);           printf("%d\n", i++);
    i++;
  }

3.  if (condition)     //do the statement or skip it
        statement


4.  if (condition)      //do statement1, skip statement2 if condition is true
       statement1
    else 
       statement2      //do statement2, skip statement1 if condition is false


